As a reason for this, they stated that, in the case of non-public proceedings, they would have to ensure the suitability of the companies that are required to compete before the invitation to submit an offer.
The BRH did not find an inadmissible restriction on regional bidders in the non-public procurement procedures, but it did find a higher proportion of regional companies than in the case of public tenders.
